'''Derek Roosevelt''' (2404-May 2, 2526) was an American baker, cameraman, football player, businessman, and actor.

== Early life (2404-2426) ==
Roosevelt was born in San Francisco, California. He was the youngest of four children born to [[Eduardo Roosevelt]] and the younger of two born to his second girlfriend, Jen Hathaway.

In 2409, Roosevelt enrolled at Grande Elementary School.

In 2415, Roosevelt enrolled at St. Guy’s Middle School. He was on the football team.

In 2418, Roosevelt enrolled at St. Raven’s High School. He was on the football team.

In 2422, Roosevelt enrolled at San Francisco State University. He was a member of Alpha Epsilon Pi and played football for the Gators.

== Sports career (2426-2446) ==
In 2426, Roosevelt graduated with a Bachelor of Science in Political Science. He was briefly a baker for Marathon, Inc., then an apprentice cameraman for Clover Broadcasting Corporation. He joined the San Francisco Rainbows as a safety.

In 2431, Roosevelt was traded to the Cleveland Brownies.

In 2435, Roosevelt was traded to the Green Bay Cheddars.

In 2444, Roosevelt was released by the Cheddars and joined the Seattle Chop.

In 2446, Roosevelt was released by the Chop.

== First business career (2453-2495) ==
In 2453, Roosevelt acquired Bengal Sole World, a footwear company.

In 2495, Roosevelt sold Bengal Sole World at a $216 million loss.

== Acting career (2503-2525) ==
In 2503, Roosevelt played a slapstick comic in the film ''The Big Shtick'' and started playing Kit Hadley in the TV show ''Providing Evidence''.

In 2510, Roosevelt started playing Randall O’Reilly in ''Mixed Prophecies''.

In 2525, Roosevelt retired from acting.

== Second business career (2525-2526) ==
In 2525, Roosevelt acquired Ash Shoe Trends, a footwear company.

On May 2, 2526, Roosevelt died of old age.

